GenCorp Inc said its board extendedto April 13 the date the rights issued under the company'sshareholder rights plan will trade separately from the commonstock.    The company said the plan, originally adopted February 18,has been extended several times since its adoption.    GenCorp said the rights plan makes it more difficult for anoutside company or person to takeover the company. The plan hasbeen extended indefinitely and to no person acquiring 20 pct ormore of the common stock prior to April 13, the company said.    The plan calls for the attachment of one preferred stockpurchase right to each common share outstanding.   On Monday, GenCorp announced it will buy up to 54 pct of itsown outstanding common shares for 130 dlrs per share. It saiddetails of the plan will be announced by the end of the week.    Reuter&#3;